        "comment": "During the last snowfall (Thursday - Friday) 25 to 40 cm of new snow fell. However, it was blown by very strong winds to leeward places of mainly southern orientations. The wind-blown snow created unstable snow slabs, pillows and overhangs. Snow and strong northerly winds are expected again during Sunday. Another 5 to 10 cm of new snow will fall in the Tatra Mountains. The snow cover will be moist to wet up to 1700 m above sea level, and up to 2000 m above sea level in case of sunny weather."
